{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In our work, we use keywords to represent entities or concepts that appear in the documents.",
    "Previous works use computational metrics such as TF-IDF or saliency [17] to extract keywords.",
    "However, computational metrics often cannot encode high-level semantics very well, causing them to sometimes unalign with human judgments.",
    "Instead, we rely on LLMs' ability to understand natural language to identify significant keywords from unstructured texts.",
    "We ensure that the keywords are salient by exploiting LLM's ability to understand semantic contexts.3) Embedding-based approaches: Finally, an important line of work organizes documents by directly modeling their semantic similarity [50]."
  ],
